{% set disclaimerCode %}<p>Sign up for our newsletter today!</p>
<p><small>By signing up, you agree to our Terms of Service and Privacy Policy.</small></p>{% endset %}

{% set copyrightCode %}<footer>
  <p><small>&copy; 2026 Vanilla Breeze. All rights reserved.</small></p>
</footer>{% endset %}

{% set sideCommentCode %}<p>This feature is available in all modern browsers. <small>(IE 11 is not supported.)</small></p>{% endset %}

{% set priceCode %}<p>$49.99 <small>per month, billed annually</small></p>{% endset %}

{% set smallCssCode %}small {
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
}{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;small&gt;</code> element represents side comments, caveats, and legal disclaimers &mdash; text that is de-emphasized relative to the main content. VB styles it with <code>var(--font-size-sm)</code>.</p>
    <p>It does not mean "make text smaller" &mdash; it has semantic meaning indicating the content is supplementary or less prominent.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Legal disclaimers:</strong> Terms of service, privacy notices</li>
      <li><strong>Copyright notices:</strong> Footer copyright text</li>
      <li><strong>Side comments:</strong> Parenthetical asides or caveats</li>
      <li><strong>Price annotations:</strong> "per month, billed annually"</li>
      <li><strong>Attribution:</strong> Source credits in blockquote captions</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>When NOT to Use</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>For multiple paragraphs of fine print &mdash; use a <code>&lt;section&gt;</code> with a smaller font class</li>
      <li>Purely for styling &mdash; use CSS <code>font-size</code></li>
      <li>For sub-headings &mdash; use heading hierarchy or <a href="/docs/elements/native/hgroup/"><code>&lt;hgroup&gt;</code></a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/small-examples.html" url="small-examples.html" title="Small print examples" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Legal disclaimer">{{ disclaimerCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Copyright notice">{{ copyrightCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Side comment">{{ sideCommentCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Price annotation">{{ priceCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Reference</h2>
    <code-block language="css" label="small CSS">{{ smallCssCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <p>VB uses the <code>--font-size-sm</code> token rather than a relative <code>em</code> value, ensuring consistency with the type scale.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Screen readers do not announce <code>&lt;small&gt;</code> differently &mdash; the content is read normally</li>
      <li>The smaller size is a visual cue only &mdash; do not hide important information in <code>&lt;small&gt;</code></li>
      <li>Legal text that users must read should be at a readable size &mdash; don't abuse <code>&lt;small&gt;</code> to make required text hard to read</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

